'''tradecraft''' refers to all the little / mundane things that spies do, like tailing someone surreptitiously, coding and decoding secret messages, the "[[dead drop]]" (which is leaving a written message somewhere in a public place when you and the recipient are probably being watched); signals like turning up or down the visor in your car, or leaving a soda can in the gutter (the recipient "dutifully" picks it up and throws it in the trash).

I found this word in the [[Wikipedia:Tom Clancy|Tom Clancy]] novels.